Name:           docker-build-cacher
Version:        1.8.2
Release:        0
Summary:        Builds a services with docker and caches all of its intermediate stages
Group:          Development/Libraries/Haskell

License:        BSD-3-Clause
Url:            https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}
Source0:        https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}-%{version}/%{name}-%{version}.tar.gz

BuildRequires:  ghc-Cabal-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-rpm-macros
BuildRequires:  ghc-containers-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-foldl-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-language-docker-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-system-filepath-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-text-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-turtle-devel

%description
A CLI tool to speed up multi-stage docker file builds by caching intermediate
stages separately, so the can be used in successive builds.


